The paper deals with formal validation and verification techniques for software architectures, which is a topic that falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The use of Promela and SPIN model checking suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also deals with runtime and deployment aspects, which could fall under the architecture (cs.AR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of a plug-in for a development tool, which could fall under the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
